{"_id":{"$oid":"58b895c47667b28f40ded741"},"author":{"userId":0,"username":"Chris Reeve","avatar":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-7pSD5TEGt4g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACI/Cqefb4i8T3E/photo.jpg?sz=50","email":"paradigmsareconstructed@gmail.com","bio":"(MC) Master of Controversies","lastTimeOnline":"1985-04-12T23:20:50.52Z"},"name":"The Wisdom of Crowds","summary":"Under the Right Circumstances, Groups can be Remarkably Intelligent, and are Often Smarter than the Smartest People in Them / However, of the Characteristics which Make them Accurate, the Academic Community has Overlooked the Importance of Diversity of Opinion / The Problem is that Groups that are Too Much Alike Find it Harder to Keep Learning, Because Each Member is Bringing Less and Less New Information to the Table / Homogeneous Groups are Great at Doing what they Do Well, but they Become Progressively Less Able to Investigate Alternatives","url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-v1R2IfYuGFU/WDt-D7yidFI/AAAAAAAAJZw/yZsTI4QQzgs1fjs7tZSic-Uo_Hi86J_OwCJoC/w3600-h5040/the-wisdom-of-crowds-bbal-card.jpg","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-v1R2IfYuGFU/WDt-D7yidFI/AAAAAAAAJZw/yZsTI4QQzgs1fjs7tZSic-Uo_Hi86J_OwCJoC/w506-h750/the-wisdom-of-crowds-bbal-card.jpg","publishDate":"2016-11-28T00:45:50.920Z","updateDate":"2017-01-03T01:42:36.005Z","category":"reform"}
{"_id":{"$oid":"58b895c47667b28f40ded742"},"author":{"userId":0,"username":"Chris Reeve","avatar":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-7pSD5TEGt4g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACI/Cqefb4i8T3E/photo.jpg?sz=50","email":"paradigmsareconstructed@gmail.com","bio":"(MC) Master of Controversies","lastTimeOnline":"1985-04-12T23:20:50.52Z"},"name":"Groupthink vs Conformity vs Social Proof vs Herding","summary":"Homogeneous Groups Are Susceptible to Groupthink Because they Become More Dependent on the Group, More Insulated from Outside Opinions, and Therefore More Convinced that the Group's Judgment Must Be Right / Groupthink Works Not So Much through Censorship as by Making Dissent Seem Somehow Improbable / Conformity, by Contrast, is a Fear of Standing Out / Herding is Similar to Conformity; it's the Sense that it is Better for Reputation to Fail Conventionally than to Succeed Unconventionally / Social Proof, on the Other Hand, is the Tendency to Assume that if Lots of People are Doing Something or Believe Something, there Must be a Good Reason Why","url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-8IjQX3qs9x0/WDttCALY_tI/AAAAAAAAJY8/mYajLWVE9CUTbi_Xp1QuIsH1BMiUPl_0wCJoC/w1800-h2520/groupthink-vs-conformity-vs-social-proof-vs-herding-bbal-card.jpg","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-8IjQX3qs9x0/WDttCALY_tI/AAAAAAAAJY8/mYajLWVE9CUTbi_Xp1QuIsH1BMiUPl_0wCJoC/w506-h750/groupthink-vs-conformity-vs-social-proof-vs-herding-bbal-card.jpg","publishDate":"2016-11-27T23:32:58.814Z","updateDate":"2017-01-03T01:42:54.617Z","category":"thinking"}
{"_id":{"$oid":"58b895c47667b28f40ded743"},"author":{"userId":0,"username":"Chris Reeve","avatar":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-7pSD5TEGt4g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACI/Cqefb4i8T3E/photo.jpg?sz=50","email":"paradigmsareconstructed@gmail.com","bio":"(MC) Master of Controversies","lastTimeOnline":"1985-04-12T23:20:50.52Z"},"name":"The Debate Over the Science Futures Market","summary":"Many of the Arguments Against a Science Futures Market are Also Arguments Against Peer Review / Some Concerns Could be Avoided by Simply Restricting the Types of Bets Accepted / The System Would Act to Discourage Insincere Debators / It Could Increase Interest in the Cutting Edge of Science / It Might Help the Public to Identify Underperforming Scientific Consensus, to Knock Down the Ideological Barriers Between Disciplines, to Reward Skepticism of Scientific Fads and Pseudoscientific Claims, and to Correct for Biases in Science Journalism","url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-mF9rycBWdDA/WDteGDtaE7I/AAAAAAAAJYE/vRz3y_W068MVi0HxGnITZZyf5BN7WlGIgCJoC/w3600-h5040/the-debate-over-the-science-futures-market-bbal-card.jpg","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-mF9rycBWdDA/WDteGDtaE7I/AAAAAAAAJYE/vRz3y_W068MVi0HxGnITZZyf5BN7WlGIgCJoC/w506-h750/the-debate-over-the-science-futures-market-bbal-card.jpg","publishDate":"2016-11-27T22:30:03.068Z","updateDate":"2017-01-03T01:43:15.416Z","category":"reform"}
{"_id":{"$oid":"58b895c47667b28f40ded744"},"author":{"userId":0,"username":"Chris Reeve","avatar":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-7pSD5TEGt4g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACI/Cqefb4i8T3E/photo.jpg?sz=50","email":"paradigmsareconstructed@gmail.com","bio":"(MC) Master of Controversies","lastTimeOnline":"1985-04-12T23:20:50.52Z"},"name":"The Science Futures Market","summary":"Although there Exist Multiple Conceptions of What it Might Look Like, they're Generally a Form of Decision Market where People can Wager Bets on Well-Crafted, Specific, Time-Limited Scientific Claims / A Social Network Dedicated to Scientific Controversies Could - in Theory at Least - Identify the True Experts for Each Specialization with Such a System / There's by Now Significant History, Philosophy and Discussion of this Crazy Idea / Could it Work as an Actual Financial Market?","url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-jbjJfTTYNTM/WDtUrmo-1CI/AAAAAAAAJXg/PVJyzLljkJ8PaKjIKKoFHGPbtG5mdqpjwCJoC/w3600-h5040/the-science-futures-market-bbal-card.jpg","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-jbjJfTTYNTM/WDtUrmo-1CI/AAAAAAAAJXg/PVJyzLljkJ8PaKjIKKoFHGPbtG5mdqpjwCJoC/w506-h750/the-science-futures-market-bbal-card.jpg","publishDate":"2016-11-27T21:49:47.449Z","updateDate":"2017-01-03T01:43:32.619Z","category":"reform"}
{"_id":{"$oid":"58b895c47667b28f40ded745"},"author":{"userId":0,"username":"Chris Reeve","avatar":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-7pSD5TEGt4g/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAACI/Cqefb4i8T3E/photo.jpg?sz=50","email":"paradigmsareconstructed@gmail.com","bio":"(MC) Master of Controversies","lastTimeOnline":"1985-04-12T23:20:50.52Z"},"name":"The Information Cascade vs the Independent Thinker","summary":"It's the Spread of an Idea that Happens when Peoples' Decisions are Made in Sequence Rather than All at Once / People May Fall in Line Because they Think that Others are Making Decisions Based on what they Know, when in Fact People are Making Decisions Based on what they Think the Others who Came Before them Knew / Instead of Aggregating All the Information Individuals have, the Cascade Becomes a Sequence of Uninformed Choices / Independent Thinkers Make the Public Information Seem Less Certain / That Encourages Others to Rely on Themselves Rather than Just Copying Others","url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-jSz1acV5KQk/WDsWS3X2ijI/AAAAAAAAJWs/8jgmVAzl9_At8R26lXDJkbedBn7h7BCTACJoC/w1800-h2520/the-information-cascade-vs-the-independent-thinker-bbal-card.jpg","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-jSz1acV5KQk/WDsWS3X2ijI/AAAAAAAAJWs/8jgmVAzl9_At8R26lXDJkbedBn7h7BCTACJoC/w506-h750/the-information-cascade-vs-the-independent-thinker-bbal-card.jpg","publishDate":"2016-11-27T17:23:57.584Z","updateDate":"2017-01-03T01:43:53.533Z","category":"reform"}
